name: Sweetwater Hills
address: 502 S Sweetwater Hills Dr, Spartanburg, South Carolina 29369
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: Pulte Homes brings new construction homes to Spartanburg with the debut of Sweetwater Hills

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: Homes in Sweetwater Hills will boast private backyards, with nearly half offering frontage along creeks that flow into the South Tyger River

amenities.name: Sweetwater Hills
amenities.description: Sweetwater Hills scenic riverfront amenity complex will feature a pool, cabana, fire pit, playground, and walking trails along the South Tyger River

amenities.name: While amenity
amenities.description: While the amenity complex is exclusive to Sweetwater Hills homeowners, its residents will also have access to the existing pool and fitness facilities

amenities.name: Sweetwater Hills
amenities.description: Sweetwater Hills is situated in the desirable Reidville area of Spartanburg, near the intersection of two well-traveled corridors, Highways 290 and 296

amenities.name: Sweetwater Hills
amenities.description: Sweetwater Hills neighbors enjoy easy access into Spartanburg’s vibrant downtown district via Hwy 296 and into alluring Greenville via I-85

amenities.name: Within minutes
amenities.description: Within 5 minutes of the community, Sweetwater Hills residents can access many everyday conveniences, plus the shopping and dining establishments that line Highways 290 and 296

amenities.name: Spartanburg continues
amenities.description: Spartanburg continues to grow in exciting new directions and recently announced the construction of a new baseball stadium that will host its own minor league team

amenities.name: Major employers
amenities.description: Major employers in the area include BMW, Spartanburg Medical Center, USC Upstate, Wofford College and Converse College

amenities.name: Adventurers business
amenities.description: Adventurers and business travelers will love the fact that Greenville-Spartanburg International Airport is within 20 minutes of the community
